## Verbatim Quotes

### Quote 1
**Context (what question prompted this):** Asked what tools he uses to keep up with his coursework.

> "Nothing. I do not use anything. I open Moodle when I remember and I open Teams when someone tells me to. I do not have a system."

**What this tells us:** He is not the technical-tinkerer type from kveladze-01. He has never been an active solver of this problem. This is a different ICP sub-segment — the *passive sufferer*.

---

### Quote 2
**Context:** Asked whether he has ever tried to set up a calendar or any reminder system.

> "Once. In first year. My mother told me to. I tried for like a week and I forgot to update it and that was it. I did not try again."

**What this tells us:** A single failed attempt at adoption two years ago, prompted by an external person (his mother), and never repeated. The pattern of learned helplessness exists even in students who never invested heavily — one failure was enough.

---

### Quote 3
**Context:** Asked how often he misses deadlines.

> "Maybe twice a semester. Sometimes three times. Last semester I failed one course and I think two of those points were from missed assignments. I am not sure exactly. I do not keep track of why I lose points."

**What this tells us:** This is the most painful single quote in any interview I have conducted. He has *failed a course* and is not entirely sure how much of that failure was attributable to platform-fragmentation misses. The cost is not only invisible to professors; it is invisible to *the student himself*. He does not have a clear causal model of his own grade penalties.

---

### Quote 4
**Context:** Asked who tells him about deadlines if he is not checking himself.

> "My friends. Or nobody. Sometimes I find out the day of. Sometimes I find out the day after, when somebody asks me where my submission is."

**What this tells us:** He is downstream of the "askers" in his social network — he is the silent counterpart to BN's group meme story. The people BN mocks (the ones who never know what is going on) are real and SH is one of them. He is also the person whose existence justifies BN's daily asking.

---

### Quote 5
**Context:** Asked whether he thinks the problem is his fault.

> "Yes. I mean, the information is there if I look. I just do not look. So it is on me. I am bad at this. Some people are good at it and I am bad at it."

**What this tells us:** Total internalization of structural failure as personal inadequacy. Compare this directly with EM (nikoloz-04): "I am the system now and the system is bad" — same self-blame, but EM at least describes herself as a *system*. SH does not even reach that abstraction. He is just "bad at this."

