## Open Questions

- How many third-year CS students fall into the passive-sufferer segment? My guess after this interview is meaningful — maybe 20-30% of the cohort.
- Would a tool *introduced to him by a friend* be adopted, even if he would never seek one out? This is the distribution-channel question.
- Is the self-blame reversible? If a tool worked for one semester would he stop describing himself as "bad at this"?

