## ICP Fit Assessment

**Strong fit.** Third-year KIU CS student, five courses (three project-based), inside the platform-fragmentation failure mode. Distinct sub-segment from the previously interviewed students (passive sufferer rather than active tinkerer or asker). Adds new signal, not duplicate.

---

## Interviewer Reflection

**Most important thing learned:**
The passive-sufferer segment exists and is qualitatively different from everyone else we have interviewed. They are not failing because their tools failed — they never had tools. They are failing because the system never demanded they build any. The implications for distribution and onboarding are large: this group cannot be reached directly, only through the askers/bridges in their own groups.

**What to do differently next time:**
Do not challenge the self-blame in the moment. I almost said "it is not really your fault" after Quote 5 and I am glad I did not. Pushing back would have changed the conversation and I would have lost the unfiltered version of his framing. Save the reframing for solution-design conversations later, not for discovery.

